    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-13T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-13T02:00:00-05:00" n="622"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d622">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4725: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-13T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 13, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 13—9:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My March 13, 9 p.m. [<hi rend="italic">a.m</hi>.]<note n="95" xml:id="d622fn95"
                        >Not printed.</note> In a further letter to <persName corresp="#p_LSMW1"
                        >Lampson</persName> dated today <persName corresp="#p_SM1"
                        >Shigemitsu</persName> states: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Our representative at Geneva wires back to me in reply to my inquiry
                            that he is not disposed to look upon Dr. <persName corresp="#p_YWW1">W.
                                W. Yen</persName>’s reservation as modifying the declaration of the
                            League resolution or as binding us in any way. As regards the expression
                            ‘complete withdrawal’ I can hardly persuade myself to read Mr.
                                <persName>Kuo Tai-chi</persName>’s meaning into the resolution as it
                            stands.</p>
                        <p>Permit me to reiterate the Japanese are prepared to enter into
                            negotiation at any time on the basis of the League resolution. It would
                            seem much better to expedite the matter if both sides stood simply on
                            the resolution itself and avoided at this state [<hi rend="italic"
                                >stage?</hi>] to bring in, conditions or matters extraneous to
                            it.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
